/*** IMAGE CAPTION*****/
.image-with-caption {
  /* Center the image and caption horizontally within its parent container */
  text-align: center;
  /* Adjust margins as needed */
  margin: 10px; 
  /* Make the figure an inline-block element so it wraps around its content 
  and can be centered on a page if needed */
  display: inline-block; 
}

.image-with-caption img {
  /* Add a border to the image itself */
  border: 2px solid #333; 
  /* Optional: add some padding between the border and the image content */
  padding: 5px;
  /* Ensure the image doesn't take up full width, allowing centering */
  display: block; 
  margin: 0 auto; /* Centers the image if the figure is wider */
}

.image-with-caption figcaption {
  /* Center the caption text (inherited from figure, but good practice to be explicit) */
  text-align: center;
  /* Optional: add styling for the caption (e.g., font size, color, margin) */
  font-size: 0.9em;
  color: #555;
  margin-top: 5px; /* Space between image and caption */
}
Complete Example
Here is a complete, working example you can copy and paste into an HTML file:
html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Image with Centered Label and Border</title>
    <style>
        .image-with-caption {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 20px;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        .image-with-caption img {
            border: 4px solid blue; /* Custom border: 4px solid blue */
            padding: 5px;
            display: block;
            margin: 0 auto; 
            max-width: 100%; /* Ensures image is responsive */
            height: auto;
        }

        .image-with-caption figcaption {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1em;
            color: #333;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <figure class="image-with-caption">
        <!-- Replace 'your-image.jpg' with your image file path -->
        <img src="picsum.photos" alt="A cute dog">
        <figcaption>A cute dog with a blue border</figcaption>
    </figure>

